Story time:  @crazy.apes_cycles and I were building bikes for @biltwell_peoples_champ 2 years ago, we were very excited to meet, and get to ride up Ortega hwy. he calls me on the way to the meet spot “hey I’m out, my shifter snapped off flush”
But I had my buddy @blue_collar_barbarian behind me in his old van with a 110 flux core so @yosemiteallencoe and i helped load kyles bike up and went to the meet up spot which happened to in a parking lot with a mex food restaurant, we plugged the welder in the bathroom of the mex food and swiped a bottle opener and welded it on there, and he was back in the game! We took off and my clutch went out first corner up the mtn. Then two corners later my brakes went out. This is a twisty road with stop lights, Kyle was going up and blocking traffic if it didn’t turn green by the time I got there. Was a hell of a day and both of us were just tryna get that $1,000 for making it so we had gas money to get home. Hope that shifter stays around and some kid tells this story when we’re gone buddy
